# UX: Single-Option Dropdown → Button

When a dropdown or context menu has **only one action**, render a **direct button** instead of a dropdown.

- Avoids extra click (open menu → click option)
- Clearer affordance
- No overflow/z-index issues with dropdown positioning

**Example**: Comment actions with only "Delete" → use a Trash icon button directly, not a ⋮ menu that opens a dropdown with one item.
